<TEXT>
suspended navajo chairman peter 
macdonald convicted last week of bribery was disqualified 
wednesday as a candidate for tribal president 
the navajo board of election supervisors decision can be 
appealed said officials of the nations largest indian tribe 
interim president leonard haskie automatically replaces 
macdonald on the presidential ballot haskie finished third in a 
primary election behind macdonald and former chairman peterson 
zah the election is nov 6 
macdonald was convicted oct 17 of bribery conspiracy and 
ethics violation charges he was accused of taking gifts and money 
from businessmen who dealt with the tribe 
he was sentenced monday to nearly six years in jail and fined 
11000 
tribal law bars people convicted of ethics violations from 
holding office for four years 
</TEXT>
