president corazon aquino has called for an orderly 
withdrawal of us forces despite the thousands of jobs and 
hundreds of millions of aid dollars linked to the bases philippine 
foreign secretary raul manglapus said his country wants to take 
over clark next year and also is seeking reductions at subic 
us negotiator richard armitage said the era of a big us 
military presence is ending but he spoke only of a phasedown not 
a phaseout 
even before the talks the united states began looking for other 
sites and has received an offer for more access to singapore 
meanwhile the us goal is to get japan to pay more of us 
forces expenses and south korea to both pay and assume a leading 
role in its own defense over the next five to 10 years 
critics in south korea including student demonstrators say the 
us military poses an obstacle to reunification with communist 
north korea 
