<TEXT>
here are facts about wednesdays parliamentary election in 
pakistan 
 
the country pakistan the worlds ninth most populous country 
was created in 1947 as a homeland for indias minority moslems it 
has seen only four popularly elected governments the military has 
ruled pakistan for more than 25 of its 43 years 
rich in resources pakistan is plagued with widespread poverty 
and illiteracy most of the countrys 110 million people are 
landless laborers earning less than 400 a year 
pakistan is burdened with a defense budget that eats 52 percent 
of the total expenditure 
 
the election more than 1300 candidates are contesting the 207 
seats reserved for moslems in the national assembly the lawmaking 
lower house of parliament another 41 candidates are contesting 10 
seats reserved for nonmoslems such as christian hindu 
zoroastrian and sikhs 
 
the issues despite a host of social and economic problems the 
only campaign issue has been benazir bhutto the former prime 
minister whose government was dismissed aug 6 on charges of 
corruption incompetence and mismanagement 
 
the candidates ms bhuttos populist centerleft pakistan 
peoples party joined forces with three smaller parties to form the 
pakistan democratic alliance her key opponent is a coalition 
called the islamic democratic alliance which embraces 18 parties 
espousing a variety of political ideologies 
there are 30 other parties contesting the election they follow 
a wide range of political principles from rightwing to farleft 
and religious fundamentalism to secession at least three parties 
are demanding independence for southern sindh province and several 
other parties were established along ethnic lines 
 
the voters there are 473 million eligibile moslem voters and 
another 14 million nonmoslem voters turnout in the november 1988 
election was 432 percent and many predict wednesdays turnout will 
be even lower 
because less than 25 percent of the population is literate 
voters will check their candidates party symbol ms bhuttos 
alliance is identified by an arrow while the symbol of the islamic 
democratic alliance is a bicycle 
