inched up 03 percent 
orders in the key category of nondefense capital goods jumped 
63 percent to 382 billion but faled to regain a 99 percent 
loss in august while these orders often are a barometer of 
business plans to expand and modernize platt suggested that much 
of them may have come from overseas 
the strength in exports probably will be one of the factors 
that will keep a recession relatively mild he said 
