frolov also released figures showing a stunning drop in the 
circulation of the newspaper that for decades was viewed as the 
most important in the country 
as of oct 1 pravda had received only 504000 subscriptions for 
next year a huge drop from its current circulation of 77 million 
the circulation drive originally scheduled to end oct 30 has 
been extended to nov 15 
frolov did not say what insulting remarks the staff had made 
but pravda employees have said they are dissatisfied with frolovs 
traditionalist views and his ties to hardline politicians 
the staffers voted three weeks ago to ask the partys central 
committee to review the newspapers leadership frolov has called 
the vote a minicoup attempt against him 
under gorbachevs policy of glasnost or greater openness 
other newspapers regularly publish articles on controversial 
political or historical themes or on popular culture 
although pravda has begun to print some articles critical of 
government officials and policies it has changed less than other 
periodicals and is one of the most orthodox communist newspapers 
its official owner is the party central committee and it 
regularly carries frontpage editorials praising and explaining 
party positions 
frolov attributed pravdas plummeting circulation both to an 
increase in its cover price which is rising from about 9 to 17 
cents and to its ownership by the party which is blamed by many 
soviets for the countrys disintegrating economy and political 
structure 
peoples attitudes toward pravda are connected with their 
attitudes toward the party he said 
frolov said he offered his resignation on tuesday to the partys 
highest bodies the central committee secretariat and politburo 
headed by gorbachev who is the party leader as well as president 
of the country 
i said i could not and did not want to work at this newspaper 
anymore frolov said 
he added that he raised the issue himself and received a 
negative response to his offer to step down 
i received full support from the politburo and the secretariat 
and of course i must and i will work at pravda he said 
frolov said he also received permission from the party leaders 
to set up a pravda association that could publish other newspapers 
sell advertising and start new ventures to raise profits and offset 
pravdas declining revenues 
he said pravda now makes a profit of about 18 million dollars a 
year but probably would become unprofitable if its circulation 
slipped below 5 million copies 
given the current status of the subscription drive it appears 
unlikely that pravda will reach the 5 million level but frolov 
said he was confident it would continue to be published and have a 
sufficient circulation to remain a worldclass newspaper 
pravda comes out seven days a week each issue is either six or 
eight pages long with no advertising 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

