chemical into the giantess geyser near old faithful 
while the force of erupting geysers sometimes ejects the debris 
karle said some become so plugged they wont erupt again 
park rangers do their best to retrieve garbage from the vents 
but most is too deep 
yellowstones thermal features are fragile and easily damaged 
walking on them carving or defacing them or removing souvenir 
pieces of formations destroys decades or centuries of intricate 
natural processes karle said 
the roughly 10000 geysers and hot springs that draw visitors to 
the nations oldest national park take many many years to build 
up and be created and just a few minutes for someone to destroy 
she said 
