deir alkamar lebanon ap thousands of people many holding 
red carnations attended the funeral wednesday of slain christian 
leader dany chamoun his wife and two young sons as they were 
buried in his hometown 
in beirut meanwhile president elias hrawis government held 
talks with militia leaders about withdrawing their forces from the 
city under a peace plan aimed at ending lebanons 15year civil 
war 
chamoun 56 and his family were gunned down at their apartment 
in beiruts eastern suburb of baabda on sunday no group has 
claimed responsibility for the slayings which were branded by both 
christian and moslem leaders as an attempt to derail the peace 
efforts 
chamoun leader of the rightwing christian national liberal 
party was a staunch ally of defeated rebel gen michel aoun his 
murder occured eight days after syrian and lebanese troops crushed 
aouns 11month mutiny in an eighthour assault that left 550 dead 
and more than 1200 wounded 
aoun has taken refuge in the french embassy he had opposed the 
peace plan because it provided no timetable for the withdrawal of 
syrian troops 40000 of whom are deployed in lebanon 
on wednesday black flags fluttered above the stone houses of 
the ancient mountain town of deir alkamar southeast of beirut as 
the four coffins were driven to the cemetery after a fourhour 
service 
chamoun his wife ingrid and their two sons tarek 7 and 
julien 5 were buried next to the tomb of his father former 
president camille chamoun the elder chamoun died a natural death 
in august 1987 
mourners were frisked by heavily armed druse militiamen of walid 
jumblatts progressive socialist party who control deir alkamar 
lebanon has lost a promise of peace an elderly woman sobbed 
at the funeral may god give us strength to end this horrible war 
once and for all 
in beirut the government issued a statement saying it intended 
to spread state authority over the capital and its environs in 
line with a peace plan endorsed by parliament aug 22 
it did not set a deadline for carrying out the plan to create a 
militiafree greater beirut 
the army would be in charge of all streets and government 
utilities all militia offices and centers would be closed said 
the statement which was issued after a threehour meeting chaired 
by hrawi 
greater beirut extends along a 15mile coastal strip and covers 
the citys eastern and southeastern suburbs 
a government source speaking on condition of anonymity said 
efforts to withdraw militias from the capital and its environs were 
now on a hot burner 
the development followed a visit to beirut on tuesday by syrian 
vice president abdulhalim khaddam the syrian army chief of staff 
and the chief of the armys military intelligence in lebanon 
the government source said a twoman government committee 
handling talks with militia leaders was instructed to work out 
the mechanism for the militia withdrawal from greater beirut 
for years moslem and christian militias have battled for 
control of the region 
the source said the militia leaders did not register any 
serious rejection of the greater beirut plan adding that it 
might be implemented as early as next week 
all the militias realize that if they dont withdraw 
peacefully the example of crushing rebel gen michel aouns mutiny 
would be repeated the government source said 
meanwhile police said the proiranian hezbollah or party of 
god withdrew from positions on the former green line along the 
eastern edge of south beirut and handed them over to hrawis army 
a police spokesman said hezbollah maintained its stronghold in 
the south beirut slums of bir abed hay madi and moawad 
other militias that maintain strongholds within the area are the 
rightwing christian lebanese forces of samir geagea the 
mainstream shiite amal movement of nabih berri and jumblatts druse 
militia 
