<TEXT>
federal health officials largest collection yet 
of aids test surveys shows the nations aids infection rates are 
highest at drug treatment clinics and lowest at blood donor 
centers 
the centers for disease control on thursday will publish the 
results of aids virus test surveys from a variety of settings 
nationwide health clinics hospitals the job corps the military 
and other places where large numbers of blood samples could be 
analyzed 
the separate surveys were considered in the absence of a 
nationwide survey for infection with hiv the virus that causes 
aids 
overall the survey data indicated the widespread yet 
extremely varied distribution of hiv the cdc reported by far 
the highest prevalence rates were found among persons known to be 
at risk specifically gay and bisexual men and users of 
intravenous drugs 
of nearly 150000 aids cases reported in the united states 59 
percent have occurred among gay or bisexual males and 21 percent 
were among iv drug abusers an additional 7 percent of aids 
patients fell into both categories and were counted separately 
the hiv prevalence surveys involved testing blood samples 
collected as far back as 1986 settings ranged from military 
recruitment centers to large urban hospitals to american red cross 
blood donation centers 
hiv infection rates in all categories were relatively low the 
worst was a median of 41 percent among clients at 54 drug 
treatment centers where by definition many are at high risk for 
aids 
federal health officials estimate that between 1 million and 15 
million americans are infected with hiv for an estimated national 
rate of about 005 percent 
one survey found the infection rate quite high in one separate 
classification high prevalences were observed among 
homosexual and bisexual men in all geographic regions the cdc 
reported 
at 103 sexuallytransmitteddisease clinics surveyed across the 
country infection rates among gay and bisexual patients ranged 
from 15 percent in two salt lake city clinics to 64 percent in two 
newark nj clinics with a median of 36 percent 
generally infection rates were higher for men than women and 
for the northeastern and southern states 
more of the surveys findings 
among about 4 million american red cross blood donors in the 
second half of 1989 the infection rate was 00084 percent or 
about 8 in 100000 that indicates not just a low number of 
infected people giving blood but also the removal of infected 
donors from the repeat donation list 
among nearly 25 million applicants for military service the 
infection rate was 012 percent or 12 of 10000 the low rate is 
not necessarily surprising as homosexuals and drug users are 
unwelcome in the military 
among 12 million childbearing women the estimated national 
infection rate was 015 percent 15 of 10000 
at 39 large urban acutecare hospitals where patients blood 
samples were analyzed the median infection rate was 07 percent 
or 7 in 1000 there was however a 70fold variation among 
individual hospitals which ranged from 01 percent to 69 percent 
rates were five times higher for men than women 15 percent to 
03 percent and somewhat higher for blacks 1 percent than for 
whites or hispanics 07 percent 
in about 100000 blood samples annually at a large diagnostic 
laboratory the hiv infection rate was 089 percent or about 9 in 
1000 
among an annual 60000 job corps entrants most of them 
disadvantaged young people the infection rate was 036 percent 
or about 4 in 1000 
at the 103 sexually transmitted disease clinics the median 
infection rate for 205000 patients was 22 percent 
at 187 womens health clinics the median infection rate for 
156000 patients was 02 percent or 2 out of 1000 
in 20 metropolitan tuberculosis clinics the median infection 
rate was 34 percent tb is a frequent complication of hiv 
infection 
