salvador which has received aid at a rate of nearly 1 million a 
day in recent years bushs top advisers have threatened to veto 
any bill that contained such an aid cut 
but the bill also contains a powerful incentive for the 
president to sign forgiveness of 67 billion in past military 
loans egypt owes the united states bush has sought to erase the 
debt as a reward to egypt which has been among the staunchest us 
allies in opposing iraqs occupation of kuwait 
