without scientific basis 
the richter scale measures the magnitude of a quake according to 
ground motion as recorded on seismographs every increase of one 
represents a tenfold increase of magnitude a quake of magnitude 5 
is capable of considerable damage and a magnitude 6 quake can 
cause severe damage 
