rep john conyers was a fiery rebel who 
disdained the establishment for much of his first quartercentury 
in congress now hes joining the other side 
i get some kidding about the fact that now im one of the 
institutional leaders that i used to criticize so much he said 
in a recent interview but my goals havent changed that much 
the black democrat from detroit is completing his second year as 
chairman of the house government operations committee 
it might seem a confining assignment for a civilrights champion 
who stood with martin luther king jr slept on sidewalks with the 
homeless and raised the possibility of impeaching president reagan 
over the irancontra affair 
but conyers 61 insists he will not abandon the causes he has 
supported since his activist days in the 1960s 
rather he can pursue his social agenda as an insider 
substituting dealmaking and quiet persuasion for the searing 
rhetoric of old 
the son of an auto worker and union organizer conyers was 
interested in politics and civil rights from his youth he chose 
law school over his other passion jazz after his father 
insisted he not become a musician 
he thought that was unthinkable wasnt steady work and 
wasnt responsible work as far as he was concerned conyers said 
i had a dickens of a time working out an arrangement to buy a 
trumpet because he thought that would start me out on the wrong 
way 
but conyers remains a big jazz fan hes even sponsoring 
legislation to forgive the 16 million tax debt of band leader 
woody hermans estate conyers says an unscrupulous business 
manager gambled away hermans money and didnt file his taxes for 
six years leaving herman penniless before his 1987 death 
unpredictability and a fierce desire for personal privacy are 
other conyers traits 
he ended his lifelong bachelorhood in june marrying 25yearold 
monica ann esters without telling his closest friends political 
associates or even his brother 
ive never gotten into his personal or social life said 
eugene gilmer of detroit a friend since 1942 its just always 
been hands off 
conyers is continuing to evolve into a congressional insider a 
year after what some considered a potentially fatal blunder his 
1989 bid to unseat veteran detroit mayor coleman young his 
errorplagued poorly organized campaign flopped and he finished 
third in the democratic primary 
he was a charismatic figure on the campaign trail dapper in 
suspenders and colorful handkerchiefs but he often showed up late 
for appointments or missed them altogether on one occasion aides 
tried to rush him to an engagement but he insisted on stopping at a 
restaurant for soul food 
after that defeat democrats spoke openly of challenging 
conyerss reelection to the house instead he was renominated for 
his house seat without opposition and is a heavy favorite to defeat 
republican raymond h shoulders in the general election 
you dont really lose any clout here in congress if you run 
