along with a special on tuna on aisle 7 and 
a sale on cat food on aisle 4 dont be surprised if your local 
supermarket features a nice deal on checking accounts 
supermarket banking something of a novelty when it first 
appeared in the 1970s has been rapidly gaining popularity over the 
last five years 
with banks under the gun to cut costs in a rocky economy there 
may be a lot more of them soon its much cheaper for a bank to set 
up a branch at a grocery counter than to operate in a tradional 
brick and mortar bank building 
and theyre apparently popular with customers 
there are currently 847 supermarket bank branches nationwide 
with most of them in the southeast and southwest said john w 
garnett executive vice president of norcross gabased 
international banking technologies a consulting firm that helps 
banks open and operate these facilities 
garnett admits that at first blush it looks mighty strange to 
see a banker holding court amid the produce and frozen pizza 
people are accustomed to seeing a 400000squarefoot 
branch he said when you walk into a supermarket and see a 
400squarefoot branch there is a perception you have to 
overcome 
we explain to customers that its backed up by the fdic 
federal deposit insurance corp that the bank is sound then 
its not a problem 
the grocery branches are fullservice operations that can do 
virtually anything a traditional bank location can do however 
they usually stay open into the evening and also do business on 
sundays garnett said 
garnetts company entered the supermarket bank business in 1983 
and now has 350 branches across the country ibt had 20 million in 
revenue last year he said 
garnett said the unconventional operations provide a great 
opportunity to attract new customers 
in a traditional bank 95 percent of your walkins are 
already customers or coming in for a specific reason he said 
ninetyfive percent in the supermarket are not your customers 
theyre not coming in for banking theyre coming in to shop 
so employees at the grocery branches have to be aggressive 
marketers these bankers walk the aisles and solicit business 
garnett said 
the chief attraction for the bank business garnett said is 
costcutting where it costs an average of 1 million up front to 
open a traditonal style bank it takes only 200000 to open a 
grocery branch he said 
ongoing costs vary from location to location said garnett 
whose exhibit drew a respectable crowd this week at the american 
bankers association convention he declined to give an average of 
monthly operating costs 
