jim devoes downhome deep voice and pot 
belly exude friendliness hes also pretty smart with an mba under 
his belt and hes good with numbers having worked in commercial 
loans for a big chicago bank 
the question is would you buy a used car from this man 
so many people have that usedcar dealer devoe is now selling 
his sales techniques to others 
every month dozens of dealers nationwide travel to this general 
motors corp factory town to hear the successful 46yearold native 
hoosier explain how they can make money selling used cars to 
customers with bad credit 
the threeday course outlines devoes buy herepay here 
philosophy a trade practice by which dealers provide the financing 
for customers the banks have turned away 
the car dealers today are having plenty of trouble and they 
need extra help said devoe who owns a chevroletcadillac 
dealership 
domestic car sales were off around 5 percent through early 
october over the previous year the prospect of a recession 
declining consumer confidence and high gasoline prices make it 
unlikely sales will rebound any time soon 
they are conditions that make buy herepay here all the more 
attractive devoe said 
he said as many as half of all car customers have some flaw in 
their credit profile that gets them rejected by banks perhaps 
theyve missed a loan payment or spent too little time in a 
community or on a job 
dealerships can set up their own lending operations that can 
finance a car purchase by these customers without as great a risk 
as a bank faces devoe said 
he gives this example involving a car selling for 2800 after 
taxes and a 300 downpayment a 2500 loan may be needed if the 
borrower doesnt pay the bank may get as little as 300 when the 
recovered car is resold and be stuck with a 2200 loss 
using that same example a dealer who may have paid only 1000 
for the car to begin with has only a 700 risk after taxes and 
downpayment with the car recovered and resold even at 300 his 
potential loss is only 400 
with a paying borrower the bank will profit from interest on 
the loan but the dealer gets interest plus the 1800 profit on 
the car at the time of the sale devoe said 
while customers get to buy a car when all seems lost they also 
pay dearly for the privilege 
interest rates many car dealers charge are well above market 
rates devoe said financing with consumer loantype rates as high 
as 25 percent is structured so the customer makes weekly or 
biweekly payments for one to three years on cars ranging in cost 
from 2995 to 5995 
devoe an mba from indiana university who worked in commercial 
loans for continental illinois bank amp trust in chicago has been 
selling cars for more than two decades he got his big break at his 
fathers dealership in marion 
devoe was attending a meeting in 1978 when another dealer told 
him about the buy herepay here plan and how it sold a lot of extra 
cars the idea became more appealing a year later when a recession 
began to set in 
devoe says an initial 19 newspaper ad grossed 8000 as cash 
flow grew devoes dealership graduated from cheaper cars and low 
sales volume to better cars and more profits 
we had to reinvent the wheel one spoke at a time during those 
10 years my god theres a lot to learn and a lot of mistakes to 
be made he said 
he started sharing those experiences with other dealers in his 
auto credit seminars beginning in 1986 he estimates more than 400 
dealer organizations and more than 2500 dealers have attended 
them 
for a 6295 fee a dealership can send as many employees it 
wants can return at any time and gets startup support a tour of 
the local gm stamping plant is thrown in for free 
ron tonkin former president of the national automobile dealers 
association said he was skeptical when he he first attended 
devoes program two years ago but he says he now has nine buy 
herepay here lots at his 10 dealerships in the portland ore 
area it took him 18 months to break even but now hes seeing 
profits 
anybody that is contemplating going into this i would 
definitely recommend they go to devoes school tonkin said 
devoe took his buy herepay here concept a step further last 
year when he created jd byrider systems a national buy herepay 
here company with 20 dealer franchises from wilmington del to 
greeley colo 
franchisees pay a 29000 fee a 3 percent royalty fee and 2 
percent for advertising 
with our experience in the business many of the dealers could 
use more support more training field men marketing programs done 
for them better operations manuals and so we feel like theres a 
big potential in franchising devoe said 
