third behind former gop sen lowell weicker who is running as an 
independent 
in oregon another state where a democrat is retiring the 
race between republican dave frohnmayer and democrat barbara 
roberts is close 
republican incumbents are in danger in at least four states 
rhode island nebraska kansas and maine 
worst for republicans is rhode island where gov ed diprete is 
far behind democrat bruce sundlun who lost to diprete in the last 
two elections 
nebraska gov kay orr and her kansas neighbor mike hayden both 
have been in trouble for tax increases but both have narrowed the 
gap by which they trailed democratic challengers 
hayden has rebounded as his democratic opponent joan finney 
has struggled to explain her opposition to abortion recent polls 
have shown hayden winning the womens vote 
maines republican gov john mckernan has also made a partial 
recovery in the polls but still faces a tough race with joseph 
brennan a former governor who replaced mckernan in congress four 
years ago 
among other republican incumbents alabamas guy hunt and iowas 
terry branstad both hold leads against strong challengers 
