those who follow the pricing of oil and refined petroleum 
products say that although rising crude prices usually bring rapid 
increases in consumer prices drops in crude usually dont work 
their way into the retail level for a few weeks 
product prices tend to lag said philip l dodge an analyst 
with nomura securities international inc people who have 
established those high prices tend to give them up grudgingly 
