ms norwood said the proposed prepackaged bankruptcy plan 
consists of two parts exchange offers and a cash infusion by the 
japanese partners 
under the exchange offers existing shareholders primarily the 
thompson family would retain a 5 percent equity position 
bondholders would receive 25 percent of the common stock and the 
japanese would purchase 70 percent of the companys common stock 
she said 
