of sears revenues posted a 76 percent gain in thirdquarter 
operating income after suffering a 32 percent decline in the second 
quarter and a 374 million loss in the first 
operating income from the retailing division totaled 892 
million sears said revenues rose to 78 billion from 76 
billion 
brennan who was given direct oversight of the merchandise group 
in early august said encouraging results in home appliances 
electronics automotive and womens apparel reflected the 
effectiveness of new retailing strategies that sears began 
implementing in march 1989 
but brennan said the performances of sears catalog home 
fashions home improvements childrens clothing and mens apparel 
departments remained sluggish 
retailing analyst walter loeb of loeb associates in new york 
said the weakness in such traditional sears strongholds as home 
improvement and home fashions indicated the merchandise group is 
still having trouble 
but sears said retailing revenues rose faster than selling and 
administrative expenses which suggests brennans costcutting 
efforts are working 
the costsaving measures include a 20 percent reduction in the 
companys catalog division staff as well as the offering of 
severance packages to 600 workers at sears corporate headquarters 
in chicago both steps took place last month 
its too early to be conclusive about it but i think this 
will be a successful program loeb said 
allstates operating income fell nearly 14 percent to 1087 
million in the third quarter reflecting catastrophic losses 
greater than historical levels dean witters operating income 
soared 60 percent to 572 million the results included a 37 
percent increase in brokerage income and 27 percent rise in income 
from discover card operations 
for the first nine months of 1990 sears earned 5234 million 
or 153 per share on sales of 404 billion that compares with 
earnings of 9064 million or 256 per share on sales of 386 
billion in the first nine months of 1989 
