industry and other concerns over the direction of the legislation 
what the aba wants in particular is the abolition of the too 
big to fail philosophy that governs bank regulation and 
legislation permitting banks to enter other lines of business 
the traditional regulatory policy ensuring large institutions 
against failure gives big banks an unfair advantage over smaller 
ones the organization believes 
the bankers want permission to move into other businesses such 
as the sale of securities insurance and real estate so they can 
compete more effectively with other financial services companies 
under the abas scenario such services would be provided by 
separately regulated divisions creating a wall that would not 
threaten the security of insured deposits yingling said 
