interior secretary manual lujan will try to 
prevent a japanese company from owning food and lodging concessions 
in americas national parks officials said wednesday 
the issue of foreign ownership surfaced in connection with a 
japanese companys possible purchase of mca inc which owns a 
subsidiary that provides concessions at yosemite national park in 
california 
james ridenour director of the national park service recently 
urged mca to sell the yosemite concessions before the japanese 
company matsushita electric industries acquires mca interior 
spokesman steve goldstein said 
he said ridenour made the request in a telephone call to mca 
chairman lew wasserman with the full support of lujan 
the secretary believes that the concessions in our national 
parks should be run by americanowned companies he wants to make 
sure mca was clear on our position said goldstein 
the mca subsidiary yosemite amp curry co has estimated holdings 
in yosemite of between 100 million and 200 million the company 
provides restaurants lodging and stores at the park under a 
contract with the national park service 
