<TEXT>
here is a brief history of the southland corp owner of the 
7eleven convenience store chain which filed for protection from 
creditors tuesday in us bankruptcy court 
 
1927 the southland co is formed in the dallas suburb of oak 
cliff from four separate companies operating eight ice plants and 
21 retail ice stations 1928 southland builds and leases 
gasoline sales stands to oil companies at its 10 totem stores 
1931 middle west utilities buys out southland shareholders a 
year later the company becomes bankrupt and a reorganization is 
ordered 
1945 companys name is changed to the southland corp a year 
later the name 7eleven is coined for growing convenience store 
chain 
1965 southland is ranked 49th among fortune magazines top 50 
merchandising firms 
1968 the 3000th 7eleven store is opened in deltona fla 
1973 7eleven enters japanese market when southland grants a 
license to japanese retailer itoyokado ltd 
1978 revenues reach 3 billion 
1983 southland purchases citgo petroleum corp for 795 
million and three years later sells half the common stock to a 
subsidiary of the stateowned petroleos de venezuela sa for 290 
million 
july 1987 southland announces the thompson family will take 
the company private in a leveraged buyout 
october 1987 the stock market crashes meaning much higher 
interest rates for the company in a turbulent bond market 
december 1987 shareholders approve the thompson familys 49 
billion leveraged buyout financed with highyield junk bonds 
march 1989 southland announces 1988 loss of 2162 million 
march 1990 southland announces 1989 loss of 131 billion 
january 1990 southland sells other half of citgo for 6615 
million to petroleos subsidiary 
march 1990 southland announces restructuring plan giving 
itoyokado 75 percent of the companys common stock and leaving 15 
percent to thompson 
june 1990 southland makes exchange offer to bondholders 
later revising plan to include a 430 million infusion from 
japanese partners and reduction of thompson family stake to 5 
percent 
oct 23 1990 bondholders reject exchange offer 
oct 24 1990 southland files for chapter 11 bankruptcy 
</TEXT>
