<TEXT>
walt disney co says its proposed nautical 
theme park and resort hotel in long beach would create 36700 jobs 
and generate 3 billion in economic activity a year 
the claims released wednesday were contained in an economic 
analysis disney presented to officials in long beach the big 
seaport south of los angeles 
disney hasnt yet decided whether to build the nautical park as 
its second gate in southern california it also is studying the 
possibility of opening a different kind of park on property it owns 
in anaheim beside disneyland setting up a bidding war of sorts 
between the cities 
the winning city would collect 62 million in taxes and fees 
much of the long beach park called port disney would be built 
on landfill brought in and dumped in long beach harbor beside the 
queen mary ocean liner now operated as a hoteltourist attraction 
by disney it would include five hotels with 3700 rooms and 
250000 square feet of retail space 
disney said its owned and operated facilities plus improvements 
to roads sewers and the rest of the nearby infrastructure would 
cost about 28 billion in 1990 dollars by the time the final phase 
is complete in 2010 
how much of that price tag will be picked up by the city will be 
a subject of negotiations disney expects the rosy economic report 
to help wring concessions from the city 
still to be completed are studies by disney and long beach on 
how smog traffic and water would be affected by the park but 
disney officials said the economic study was a milestone 
its a very important step for us it will enable us to begin 
financial negotiations with the city of long beach alan g 
epstein vice president of disney development co said in a 
telephone interview from the company headquarters in burbank 
disney presented its concept for the long beach park in july it 
is less far along in its studies for the possible second park in 
anaheim epstein said a facility similar to epcot center in florida 
is among the proposals for the location beside disneyland 
officials in both cities say they are eager to win the new park 
however its impact on long beach is less clear than for anaheim 
long beach officials citing allegations of disney 
highhandedness with florida cities have said they will insist the 
city as well as disney must benefit 
long beach mayor ernie kell said his first reaction was that 
disneys report is very impressive 
but this is just one step in about 100 steps before we are in 
a position to say this is going to work kell said 
just to bring the landfill over from catalina island is 
going to cost about 300 million kell said thats just the 
starter and then we have infrastructure to look at sewer lines 
water the trucks on the long beach freeway that will have to be 
rerouted 
the economic study prepared by the los angeles consulting firm 
kotin regan amp mouchly inc for disney said port disney would 
create more than 36700 permanent jobs in southern california 
including 23900 in long beach plus many more jobs during 
construction port disney itself would employ about 12400 people 
making it the second largest private employer in long beach 
generate about 17 billion in new economic activity each year 
in long beach as part of the 3 billion total for the fivecounty 
greater los angeles region 
produce more than 62 million in new taxes and fees to los 
angeles county and the city of long beach 
with this substantial increase in annual revenues long beach 
would be able to fund not only the public infrastructure required 
to accommodate the project but solutions to some of its most 
pressing problems epstein said in a statement 
kell who told the associated press in an earlier interview that 
